comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-06T23:08:42.681Z",codex-agent,Duplicate-check evidence rerun via context list-open list-in-progress list-blocked and focused searches; no open direct equivalent for clear-tests plus test replacement.
  "2026-04-06T23:15:34.488Z",codex-agent,"Implementation start: add deterministic single-transaction linked-test replacement semantics in pm update (explicit replace path and/or clear+seed transaction support), preserve existing conflict checks for unrelated collection clears, and add unit/integration regression coverage for allowed and disallowed flag combinations."
  "2026-04-06T23:25:00.802Z",codex-agent,"Implemented deterministic linked-test replacement ergonomics via new --replace-tests update flag. Behavior: requires at least one --test entry, clears/reseeds tests atomically in one mutation transaction, rejects --replace-tests with --clear-tests, and preserves legacy --clear-tests + --test conflict guard. Also updated contracts/schema, shell completion surfaces (bash/zsh/fish), Pi wrapper mapping, and release-readiness expectations. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/update-command.spec.ts tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts tests/unit/pi-agent-extension.spec.ts tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (passed)."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-06T23:08:42.681Z",codex-agent,Prefer explicit replacement flag or deterministic combined semantics while preserving existing conflict guards for other linked collections.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-06T23:08:42.681Z",codex-agent,Linked-array mutation ergonomics need transaction-level shortcuts to avoid error-prone per-entry loops.
